## Why I Chose This Issue

In OWASP Noir's src/deliver/send_proxy.cr, two collection-emptiness checks use .size > 0 instead of Crystal's idiomatic .empty? pattern, which is used consistently everywhere else in the codebase. 
This inconsistency reduces readability and goes against the project's own conventions. 

I chose this issue because it is a well-scoped, low-risk change that lets me focus on learning the open-source contribution workflow without needing deep familiarity with the language or the project's security logic. 
Through this contribution, I hope to practice the mechanics of a real OSS workflow and build confidence for tackling larger issues in the future.

